Expected: rd_valid=1 every cycle after rd_en=1 when HIGH queue non-empty
Actual: rd_valid missing on alternating cycles, data_op advances without rd_valid
Impact: Consumer logic misses every other HIGH priority read transaction — silent data loss
Suspected RTL Location: rd_valid generation logic for high priority path, design.sv around line 285

BUG FIFO-002
Title: rd_valid intermittently not asserted on MEDIUM priority reads
Severity: Critical
Found By: mixed_test
Design File: design.sv line 313 (med_rd assertion)
Description:
Same class of bug as FIFO-001 but affecting the MEDIUM priority read path. When high priority queue is empty and rd_en=1 with medium priority items present, rd_valid is intermittently suppressed. DUT's own med_rd assertion at design.sv:313 confirms the location.
